<TITLE> PM says to persuade Rahul Gandhi to join cabinet </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW DELHI, May 16 (bdnews24.com/ Reuters) - Prime Minister Manmohan Singh said he would try to persuade Rahul Gandhi, scion of the Gandhi family, to join the cabinet after the ruling Congress-led coalition's win in a general election. "It is my wish that he should be in the cabinet. But I will have to persuade him," Singh told reporters. A new government must be formed by June 2.
